OL,3,C'Amazing' school trip could become
OL,4,Ccompulsory but not everyone agrees
OL,6,FThe bill has been put forward by
OL,7,FConservative MS Sam Rowlands, who
OL,8,Fsaid: "There are some longer-term
OL,9,Fbenefits to these types of experiences
OL,10,Fwhich I think government should
OL,11,Fseriously consider because what we
OL,12,Fneed to ensure is that children have
OL,13,Fan active lifestyle which can help
OL,14,Fthem in the long run in terms of their
OL,15,Fphysical health, and we know the
OL,16,Fmental health challenges our young
OL,17,Fpeople are facing at the moment."
