OL,3,C'Amazing' school trip could become
OL,4,Ccompulsory but not everyone agrees
OL,6,FIf passed, this bill would cost an
OL,7,Festimated #20million each year to
OL,8,Fimplement, something which opponents
OL,9,Fof the bill fear could have an adverse
OL,10,Fimpact on the education sector.
OL,12,FLaura Doel, national secretary for the
OL,13,FNational Association of Head Teachers
OL,14,F(NAHT) Cymru, said: "The problem we
OL,15,Fhave with the bill is that it seeks to
OL,16,Ftake money from local authorities
OL,17,Fwhich are already cash-strapped and
OL,18,Fput that money in outdoor education.
