OL,3,C'Amazing' school trip could become
OL,4,Ccompulsory but not everyone agrees
OL,6,F"When you've got schools fundraising
OL,7,Ffor the basics, when you've got
OL,8,Fschools making redundancies of
OL,9,Fteachers and teaching assistants, we
OL,10,Fcannot afford to take away any of that
OL,11,Ffrontline funding from the delivery of
OL,12,Fcore education."
OL,14,FShe added that while she supports the
OL,15,Fspirit of the bill and appreciates the
OL,16,Fvalue of outdoor education, she does
OL,17,Fnot believe it is workable in the
OL,18,Fcurrent climate.
