OL,3,C'Amazing' school trip could become
OL,4,Ccompulsory but not everyone agrees
OL,6,FThe Welsh Government shares NAHT
OL,7,FCymru's concerns, having indicated
OL,8,Fthat while it supports residential
OL,9,Foutdoor education it will not back
OL,10,Fthis bill due to its cost implications.
OL,12,FBut supporters still believe the
OL,13,Fbenefits of outdoor education
OL,14,Frepresent good value for money and
OL,15,Finsist this kind of experience should
OL,16,Fbe a right rather than a privilege.
